---
title: Vietnamese-Style Pork & Slaw with Crispy Shallots & Fried Egg
description: First impressions are everything and this Vietnamese inspired bowl doesn’t disappoint. A fried egg looks and tastes fabulous, especially on oyster sauce, garlic ginger and lemongrass pork. Underneath this flashy exterior is a creamy slaw and tangy, yet slightly sweet, pickled onion. We’re sure this dish will be on here for many more dinners to come.

 *This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 30g carbohydrates per serving.*

